Comment_glosser: Blazek (2009) confirms the subtractive numerals in Dravidian languages.
Here the form of 10 varies from the actual 10 which is ɑttu
The form for 2 varies from the actual form 2 which is erəɖu
It’s a mistake, 60 here should be ‘ərɑʋəttu’, which is 5⋅10
It’s a mistake, 70 here should be ‘ijubəttu’, which is 7⋅10
It’s a mistake, 71 here should be ‘ijubəttɪ ondu’, which is (7⋅10)+1
It’s a mistake, 72 here should be ‘ijubəttɪ ereɖu’, which is (7⋅10)+2
It’s a mistake, 73 here should be ‘ijubəttɪ mu:ru’, which is (7⋅10)+3
It’s a mistake, 74 here should be ‘ijubəttɪ nɑ:ku’, which is (7⋅10)+4
It’s a mistake, 75 here should be ‘ijubəttu əidu’, which is (7⋅10)+5
It’s a mistake, 76 here should be ‘ijubəttɪ ɑ:ru’, which is (7⋅10)+6
It’s a mistake, 77 here should be ‘ijubəttɪ i:ju’, which is (7⋅10)+7
It’s a mistake, 78 here should be ‘ijubəttɪ eʈʈʊ’, which is (7⋅10)+8
It’s a mistake, 79 here should be ‘ijubəttɪ ombəttu’, which is (7⋅10)+(1′-10)
